title: Gold Climbs to One-Week High on U.S. Trade Gap, Weak Dollar
text:
Gold prices rose to a one-week high on Tuesday after weaker U.S. trade data weighed on the dollar and fanned tradersâ€™ hopes that the Federal Reserve might delay increasing interest rates till later this year.
The most actively traded contract, for December delivery, was recently up $9.50, or 0.8%, at $1,147.10 a troy ounce on the Comex division of the New York Mercantile Exchange.
